      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's definitely not just \"getting older,\" but it's also not a crisis you need to panic over. Your current breathing pattern suggests your asthma is becoming less well-controlled, which is a sign you need to take action. You should immediately look at increasing your maintenance inhaler dosage, perhaps adding a short-burst steroid puffer to your routine, and definitely make an appointment with your primary care physician to review your current treatment plan.",
